## Original problem

The Hint button appeared to do nothing. Root cause was **BFS blocking the JS thread** (~1.3s avg, ~2.5s hard boards) with no loading feedback ‚Äî not a dead code path.

## Architecture (current flow)

```
GameControls.onHint
  ‚Üí usePuzzleGame.handleHint
      ‚Üí setHintLoading(true) immediately
      ‚Üí InteractionManager.runAfterInteractions(...)
          ‚Üí findHintMoveSequence(board, size, excludedReverseMove, 3)
          ‚Üí dispatch SHOW_HINT { index, sequence }
          ‚Üí setHintLoading(false)
  ‚Üí PuzzleBoard highlights tiles via hintIndex / hintSequence
  ‚Üí CLEAR_HINT after 3s timeout

Cancellation: requestId ref invalidates stale searches on board change,
new hint tap, or unmount.
```

Key files:
- `src/utils/puzzleLogic.ts` ‚Äî IDA\* solver (`findHintMoveSequence3x3`, `getHintFirstMoves`)
- `src/hooks/usePuzzleGame.ts` ‚Äî async `handleHint`, `hintLoading`, `cancelHintSearch`
- `src/components/GameControls.tsx` ‚Äî Hint button with spinner + "Thinking‚Ä¶"
- `src/components/PuzzleBoard.tsx` ‚Äî maps `hintSequence` to tile badges
- `src/components/Tile.tsx` ‚Äî hint border + numbered badge UI
- `App.tsx` ‚Äî wires `hintLoading` to `GameControls`

## Completed changes

### Phase 1 ‚Äî IDA\* solver (`puzzleLogic.ts`)

- Replaced full BFS with **IDA\*** using `getManhattanDistance` heuristic
- Mutable path array in recursion to reduce allocations
- Returns first `maxMoves` of optimal path to solved state

**Benchmarks (after fix, 50 random 3√ó3 boards):**

| Metric | BFS (before) | IDA\* (after) |
|--------|--------------|---------------|
| Median | ~840ms | ~20ms |
| Average | ~1300ms | ~122ms |
| Hard board | ~2500ms | ~158ms |
| Max | ‚Äî | ~915ms |

### Phase 2 ‚Äî Async hint computation (`usePuzzleGame.ts`, `GameControls.tsx`, `App.tsx`)

- `hintLoading` state set synchronously on tap
- Solver runs in `InteractionManager.runAfterInteractions`
- Request ID + `cancelHintSearch()` on board change, re-tap, unmount
- Hint button shows `ActivityIndicator` + "Thinking‚Ä¶", disabled while loading

### Phase 3 ‚Äî Exclusion logic (`puzzleLogic.ts`, `usePuzzleGame.ts`)

`getHintFirstMoves()` rules:
- Skip undo tile only when **other moves exist**
- Always allow undo when it **solves in one step**
- Allow sole neighbor even if it is the undo tile
- `handleHint` deps include `state.history`

